1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:25,130 --> 00:01:28,940
[War of Faith]

3
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:31,900
[Episode 28]

4
00:01:32,140 --> 00:01:32,780
Sir.

5
00:01:34,570 --> 00:01:35,650
I don't know

6
00:01:35,650 --> 00:01:37,570
when you retrieved the transaction list

7
00:01:37,570 --> 00:01:38,620
because last night,

8
00:01:38,620 --> 00:01:39,770
the archive where the list was stored

9
00:01:39,770 --> 00:01:41,289
was already burned down by Yu Zhiying.

10
00:01:41,289 --> 00:01:42,490
The one I have here

11
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:44,430
was saved from the fire.

12
00:01:49,259 --> 00:01:50,330
The culprit is not

13
00:01:50,330 --> 00:01:51,860
some Japanese speculator.

14
00:01:52,630 --> 00:01:54,640
It's the wife of a high-ranking Treasury Department official.

15
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:56,440
She is the biggest market maker.

16
00:02:08,430 --> 00:02:09,539
There's also Yu Shiqing,

17
00:02:09,539 --> 00:02:10,330
Kang Shaojie,

18
00:02:10,330 --> 00:02:11,260
Zhang Mingquan,

19
00:02:11,410 --> 00:02:12,530
and Huang Daowu.

20
00:02:12,550 --> 00:02:13,680
They worked together

21
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,610
to maliciously act as the opponents of the Central Bank

22
00:02:15,610 --> 00:02:17,870
and earned up to 15 million silver coins.

23
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,850
These are all the transaction lists and records.

24
00:02:19,850 --> 00:02:21,250
The evidence is all here.

25
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:25,050
These are rumors.

26
00:02:25,340 --> 00:02:25,940
Sir.

27
00:02:26,550 --> 00:02:27,110
Sir.

28
00:02:27,810 --> 00:02:29,600
We already have solid evidence.

29
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:31,730
If we expose this report to the public,

30
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,310
the public will believe us.

31
00:02:33,310 --> 00:02:35,750
Ruolai, what exactly do you want?

32
00:02:35,770 --> 00:02:37,640
I just think it's unfair. I want justice.

33
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:38,170
Justice?

34
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:39,810
I'll give you justice after this passes.

35
00:02:39,810 --> 00:02:41,100
It's chaotic enough now.

36
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:42,130
If you insist on acting alone,

37
00:02:42,130 --> 00:02:43,280
the country will be the one that's harmed.

38
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,970
Do you understand this?

39
00:02:44,970 --> 00:02:45,380
No

40
00:02:45,380 --> 00:02:46,770
and I don't want to either.

41
00:02:46,770 --> 00:02:47,850
You're trying to cover up a blatant mistake

42
00:02:47,850 --> 00:02:48,850
to help the tyrants, sir.

43
00:02:48,850 --> 00:02:49,850
I told you before

44
00:02:49,850 --> 00:02:50,650
that politics

45
00:02:50,930 --> 00:02:51,810
is the art of compromise.

46
00:02:51,810 --> 00:02:53,140
I don't want to compromise.

47
00:02:53,140 --> 00:02:55,170
They must be punished for their evil deeds.

48
00:02:55,170 --> 00:02:56,630
Even if I have to risk my life,

49
00:02:56,630 --> 00:02:58,290
I will fight them to the death.

50
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:03,140
Wei Ruolai,

51
00:03:04,410 --> 00:03:06,010
if you insist on your own way,

52
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,930
don't blame me for being cruel.

53
00:03:08,940 --> 00:03:09,940
From now on,

54
00:03:10,490 --> 00:03:12,210
I am no longer your mentor.

55
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,000
Our ties

56
00:03:15,810 --> 00:03:17,090
are severed.

57
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:41,500
Putting all the blame

58
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,140
on a Japanese speculator?

59
00:03:43,329 --> 00:03:44,930
How could they think of that?

60
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:48,480
The people are the most united right now

61
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:49,380
and yet, they did this.

62
00:03:49,380 --> 00:03:51,110
Chiang must be crazy for money.

63
00:03:51,460 --> 00:03:52,829
A tyrannical warlord

64
00:03:52,860 --> 00:03:54,350
needs money and guns.

65
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:56,810
To them, the lives of the people

66
00:03:56,930 --> 00:03:57,610
are just pawns

67
00:03:57,610 --> 00:03:59,470
that can be sacrifice at any time.

68
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:00,810
The most important thing now

69
00:04:00,810 --> 00:04:02,490
is to send Wei Ruolai's investigation report

70
00:04:02,490 --> 00:04:03,890
to the major newspapers.

71
00:04:03,940 --> 00:04:04,780
I'll do it.

72
00:04:05,730 --> 00:04:07,040
There are many leftist newspapers in Shanghai.

73
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:08,190
They will cooperate.

74
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:10,320
This time, we must show the people

75
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:13,510
Chiang and the Nanjing government's true natures.

76
00:04:33,810 --> 00:04:34,490
Xu,

77
00:04:34,909 --> 00:04:36,630
I don't dare to publish this.

78
00:04:37,659 --> 00:04:38,710
Don't worry.

79
00:04:39,159 --> 00:04:41,159
These records are definitely real.

80
00:04:41,580 --> 00:04:44,240
The background information has been thoroughly investigated

81
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:45,230
and verified.

82
00:04:47,830 --> 00:04:50,659
The people of Shanghai are suffering because of the treasury bills.

83
00:04:50,659 --> 00:04:52,990
Countless families have been destroyed.

84
00:04:56,659 --> 00:04:58,570
I can publish it,

85
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:02,590
but I'm afraid it'll infuriate Nanjing.

86
00:05:02,900 --> 00:05:04,050
They'll shut down

87
00:05:04,340 --> 00:05:07,200
the newspaper agency and even arrest journalists.

88
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:08,950
Can it be printed privately

89
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:13,560
and distributed to the public with the newspaper's circulation channels?

90
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:14,280
Xu,

91
00:05:14,340 --> 00:05:15,980
this won't have enough credibility.

92
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:19,220
A privately printed paper would look like a rumor.

93
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:21,010
No one would believe it.

94
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:25,760
Is there any easier or faster way

95
00:05:26,140 --> 00:05:28,600
to let the people know what Nanjing has done?

96
00:05:28,610 --> 00:05:29,860
There is,

97
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:32,280
but you might take some risks.

98
00:05:33,110 --> 00:05:35,290
[Hong Fang Clothing Shop]

99
00:05:56,260 --> 00:05:56,890
Wei?

100
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:01,830
Why are you here?

101
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:04,700
Do you need more clothes?

102
00:06:06,020 --> 00:06:06,900
Sort of.

103
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,660
Can we talk privately?

104
00:06:11,930 --> 00:06:12,570
Come in.

105
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,140
Mr. Xu,

106
00:06:21,010 --> 00:06:22,010
I want to ask you

107
00:06:22,530 --> 00:06:23,390
to do me a favor.

108
00:06:23,990 --> 00:06:24,980
No need to be so formal.

109
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:26,110
What can I do for you?

110
00:06:26,540 --> 00:06:27,880
I want you to help me find a media outlet

111
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,010
to publish a report.

112
00:06:29,620 --> 00:06:31,620
The Nanjing government and rich merchants of Shanghai

113
00:06:31,620 --> 00:06:33,500
worked together to manipulate the treasury bills.

114
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,159
They screwed over the banks and the people,

115
00:06:35,159 --> 00:06:37,020
earning 15 million silver coins.

116
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,810
I'm just a tailor,

117
00:06:42,180 --> 00:06:43,530
not a reporter.

118
00:06:46,310 --> 00:06:47,670
I remember your voice.

119
00:06:50,780 --> 00:06:52,320
That night, you asked from behind me

120
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:54,050
to give the seal to Li Shengda.

121
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:55,970
You lowered your voice,

122
00:06:55,970 --> 00:06:57,700
but I could still tell it's you.

123
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:01,130
I'm sorry.

124
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:03,070
I don't know what you're talking about.

125
00:07:03,070 --> 00:07:03,950
Mr. Xu,

126
00:07:04,290 --> 00:07:06,370
only the Communist Party can help me.

127
00:07:09,020 --> 00:07:09,930
Mr. Wei,

128
00:07:11,190 --> 00:07:12,990
you really got the wrong person.

129
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:15,410
Miss Shen said

130
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:17,090
she can publish the report on the newspaper.

131
00:07:17,090 --> 00:07:18,660
Then why don't you go to her?

132
00:07:18,660 --> 00:07:20,170
Because her identity is too special.

133
00:07:20,170 --> 00:07:21,420
I can only come to you.

134
00:07:21,570 --> 00:07:22,300
You are the only communist

135
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:23,330
that I know.

136
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:24,720
I'm not.

137
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,740
How many times have I told you?

138
00:07:28,740 --> 00:07:30,020
Are you deaf?

139
00:07:31,180 --> 00:07:32,710
So you're afraid, right?

140
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:37,320
Fine.

141
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:39,000
I'll figure it out myself.

142
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:40,780
I don't believe that among all the media outlets in Shanghai,

143
00:07:40,780 --> 00:07:42,980
not one dares to stand up for the people.

144
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:51,310
Don't be impulsive.

145
00:07:51,970 --> 00:07:53,130
This matter

146
00:07:53,150 --> 00:07:54,280
is too complicated.

147
00:07:55,370 --> 00:07:57,810
It's beyond the ability of a newspaper agency.

148
00:07:57,810 --> 00:07:59,210
Then I'll go on the street and write a poster.

149
00:07:59,210 --> 00:08:01,340
Then you will be arrested immediately

150
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:02,340
and this time,

151
00:08:02,780 --> 00:08:03,980
no one can rescue you.

152
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:06,410
I know you're not afraid of death,

153
00:08:06,930 --> 00:08:08,390
but even if you get killed,

154
00:08:08,770 --> 00:08:11,100
you still won't be able to spread the news.

155
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:13,540
Do you think your death will be worth it?

156
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:19,360
I found a newspaper agency earlier.

157
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,430
The editor-in-chief didn't dare to publish it,

158
00:08:21,430 --> 00:08:22,750
but he gave me an idea.

159
00:08:24,510 --> 00:08:25,350
What idea?

160
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:28,030
The law doesn't punish the public.

161
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:29,550
If one newspaper agency

162
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:30,330
publishes it,

163
00:08:30,330 --> 00:08:31,530
they'll be shut down.

164
00:08:31,770 --> 00:08:33,530
But if everyone publishes it,

165
00:08:34,390 --> 00:08:36,380
the Nanjing government won't be able to shut everyone down.

166
00:08:36,380 --> 00:08:38,440
Let's hold a press conference first.

167
00:08:38,780 --> 00:08:40,900
We must have hundreds of media agencies

168
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:42,230
get the news on the spot.

169
00:08:42,890 --> 00:08:44,059
What if

170
00:08:44,410 --> 00:08:46,010
they still won't publish it?

171
00:08:47,730 --> 00:08:48,660
They will.

172
00:08:49,580 --> 00:08:51,310
Reporters have their dignity.

173
00:08:51,660 --> 00:08:53,460
They may be cowardly in private,

174
00:08:53,740 --> 00:08:55,280
but if they continue to play dumb

175
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:56,410
about such a big news

176
00:08:57,330 --> 00:08:58,280
in front of their peers,

177
00:08:58,280 --> 00:09:00,610
how will they be able to work in the future?

178
00:09:07,930 --> 00:09:10,310
[New Dance Hall]

179
00:09:10,410 --> 00:09:13,440
[Hong Fang Clothing Shop]

180
00:09:14,890 --> 00:09:15,890
How did he know?

181
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:17,960
He's always known.

182
00:09:18,260 --> 00:09:19,320
He just never said.

183
00:09:19,820 --> 00:09:21,220
He heard my voice before.

184
00:09:24,950 --> 00:09:27,750
He's really good at hiding.

185
00:09:29,450 --> 00:09:30,410
He's very angry.

186
00:09:31,290 --> 00:09:33,690
He saw clearly the darkness and corruption

187
00:09:34,290 --> 00:09:35,370
of the Kuomintang.

188
00:09:35,370 --> 00:09:37,750
This country must change.

189
00:09:39,420 --> 00:09:40,180
So...

190
00:09:40,790 --> 00:09:43,140
I want him to join the next step of the operation.

191
00:09:43,140 --> 00:09:43,900
No.

192
00:09:44,410 --> 00:09:45,940
He's not a party member yet.

193
00:09:46,170 --> 00:09:47,050
I told him

194
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:50,030
we'll hold a press conference,

195
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:51,290
but we fear

196
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:52,890
the news will be leaked

197
00:09:53,380 --> 00:09:55,900
and the Investigation and Arrest Unit will cause trouble.

198
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:57,960
He thought about it for three minutes

199
00:09:58,020 --> 00:09:59,220
and drafted a plan.

200
00:10:07,810 --> 00:10:11,470
[Hong Fang Clothing Shop]

201
00:10:12,210 --> 00:10:14,300
How did he come up with such a plan?

202
00:10:14,940 --> 00:10:16,380
I was surprised too.

203
00:10:16,730 --> 00:10:18,450
This kid

204
00:10:19,690 --> 00:10:21,420
was born to be a revolutionist.

205
00:10:37,910 --> 00:10:38,590
Ruolai,

206
00:10:38,610 --> 00:10:39,400
are you done?

207
00:10:39,870 --> 00:10:41,270
What are you printing?

208
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:46,610
At twelve o'clock on Thursday,

209
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:49,480
the construction treasury bill's dark truth

210
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:52,140
will be announced at the intersection

211
00:10:52,180 --> 00:10:53,990
outside Great Star Theater.

212
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:55,630
All are welcome.

213
00:10:56,870 --> 00:10:57,730
Ruolai,

214
00:10:57,890 --> 00:10:58,940
if you do this,

215
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,440
you will be arrested.

216
00:11:02,470 --> 00:11:04,070
If it benefits the country, I can risk my life.

217
00:11:04,070 --> 00:11:06,160
How can I go toward fortune and avoid misfortune?

218
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:07,560
I used to think the national affairs

219
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:09,560
had nothing to do with us commoners.

220
00:11:10,060 --> 00:11:11,180
But now, I feel that

221
00:11:11,650 --> 00:11:13,060
if I don't do anything,

222
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:15,320
I'll feel guilty towards my conscience

223
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:17,920
and the friends and family who were affected.

224
00:11:49,170 --> 00:11:50,010
Chief Editor Huang,

225
00:11:50,010 --> 00:11:50,890
Your letter.

226
00:11:50,130 --> 00:11:51,940
[309 Hankou Road, Shandong Middle Road]

227
00:11:50,130 --> 00:11:51,940
[To Mr. Huang Yijun of Shen Bao Newspaper]

228
00:11:54,110 --> 00:11:54,990
Thank you.

229
00:12:02,230 --> 00:12:04,430
[Lin Qiaosong was reinstated and returned to the Investigation and Arrest Unit due to his contributions in the battle against Japan]

230
00:12:02,530 --> 00:12:04,170
Who sent you this letter?

231
00:12:04,250 --> 00:12:05,650
A reporter this morning.

232
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,580
It's one of my drinking buddies.

233
00:12:08,580 --> 00:12:10,070
He felt that the letter was problematic,

234
00:12:10,070 --> 00:12:11,270
so he told me immediately.

235
00:12:11,270 --> 00:12:12,330
He also asked about it.

236
00:12:12,330 --> 00:12:13,700
Many reporters have received it.

237
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:14,780
Many reporters?

238
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,130
Have you found out who sent the letter?

239
00:12:17,130 --> 00:12:18,130
It's not written,

240
00:12:18,450 --> 00:12:20,700
but the postmark is from Zhabei.

241
00:12:20,260 --> 00:12:22,390
[No. 442, Route Lafayette, Shanghai]

242
00:12:20,260 --> 00:12:22,390
[To the editorial department of the Life Post]

243
00:12:21,110 --> 00:12:22,640
I've sent someone to check.

244
00:12:23,820 --> 00:12:25,580
Twelve at noon on Thursday.

245
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:29,160
They're so high profile.

246
00:12:29,670 --> 00:12:32,070
Aren't they scared of getting caught by us?

247
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:33,270
I guess

248
00:12:33,740 --> 00:12:35,400
they invited many reporters,

249
00:12:35,660 --> 00:12:37,990
so they think we won't dare to arrest them.

250
00:12:40,330 --> 00:12:41,060
Yes.

251
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:42,940
There'll be many reporters there.

252
00:12:42,940 --> 00:12:43,930
If we arrest them on the spot,

253
00:12:43,930 --> 00:12:45,730
it will make us seem guilty.

254
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:49,670
Sir,

255
00:12:50,740 --> 00:12:52,560
if it's not convenient to act in public,

256
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:53,820
I'll go to the Axe Gang.

257
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:55,960
We'll just say that the people wouldn't pay their debts,

258
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:57,510
so the Axe Gang attacked them.

259
00:12:57,510 --> 00:13:00,150
Then we'll handle the case as malicious public security,

260
00:13:00,150 --> 00:13:03,150
go through the motions, and release them in a few days.

261
00:13:03,780 --> 00:13:04,780
You've improved.

262
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:05,680
Let’s do it.

263
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:06,620
Find Qian Shaoliang directly.

264
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:08,020
Have him to send more men.

265
00:13:08,170 --> 00:13:08,860
The money

266
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:10,820
will be paid by the Garrison Command.

267
00:13:10,820 --> 00:13:11,260
Yes.

268
00:13:34,770 --> 00:13:37,730
[Wen Youtian's Tomb]

269
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:42,920
Did Wen send you a message in your dream?

270
00:13:46,020 --> 00:13:47,740
I dreamed of him last night.

271
00:13:49,730 --> 00:13:51,730
He asked me to apologize to you.

272
00:13:52,260 --> 00:13:55,120
He said he borrowed a pair of leather shoes from you.

273
00:13:56,060 --> 00:13:59,200
He wanted to wear them for a few days before returning them,

274
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,550
but the sole fell off

275
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:02,880
and he didn't have time to fix it.

276
00:14:03,930 --> 00:14:06,050
He told you to buy a new pair.

277
00:14:06,950 --> 00:14:09,680
He'll find a chance to pay it back in his next life.

278
00:14:15,830 --> 00:14:17,550
Wen was my best friend.

279
00:14:19,810 --> 00:14:21,940
I wanted to rent a nice house in Huangpu

280
00:14:22,870 --> 00:14:25,150
after making money

281
00:14:25,820 --> 00:14:27,550
and have him live with me there.

282
00:14:28,710 --> 00:14:30,570
There are many rich people there.

283
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:33,460
